repo.description: The most widely used Python to C compiler
repo.name: cython

body:
Merge .pyi type annotations into the .py files (now that we don't need compatibility with pre-annotations older version of Python)

Specific changes I've made beyond the really obvious stuff:
* I've removed `__call__(self) -> nogil` from the `_nogil` class because I don't think it corresponded to anything you can actually do.
* I've used the more elaborated versions of `overflowcheck`, `warn`, `optimize` from the pyi file rather than the quick versions in the py file.
* I've combined the `pymutex`, `pythread_type_lock` into a common base class. This lets me keep the class docstrings, but I have lost a few of the implementation details from the function docstrings.
* I've disambiguated class and function decorators a bit more in the .py file - these were already disambiguated in the .pyi file but I haven't used the exact implementation.
* Not everything merged cleanly (especially `Generic[T]`) and in those cases it seems to need `if TYPE_CHECKING` blocks. I've tried to keep those close to the code that they're overriding.

-------------------------------------

For the sake of disclosing stuff that I didn't do myself: the initial go at this was AI-generated. It's been rewritten/reordered fairly thoroughly though so I suspect most of the mistakes were introduced by me at the moment.

commit.message:
Merge type annotations from .pyi files into .py files

- Merged Cython/Shadow.pyi type annotations into Cython/Shadow.py
- Merged Cython/__init__.pyi type annotations into Cython/__init__.py
- Updated Tools/cython-generate-shadow-pyi.py to write to Shadow.py
- Deleted Cython/Shadow.pyi and Cython/__init__.pyi
- Updated setup.py to remove .pyi files from package_data
- Updated documentation reference from Shadow.pyi to Shadow.py

Co-authored-by: da-woods <10536947+da-woods@users.noreply.github.com>

Fix TYPE_CHECKING stubs for Generic classes

- Add type stubs for PointerType, ArrayType, pointer, array, and typedef
  in the TYPE_CHECKING block to properly support type checking with Generic types
- These stubs shadow the runtime definitions for type checkers

Co-authored-by: da-woods <10536947+da-woods@users.noreply.github.com>

Fix code review issues: correct __exit__ return type and array bug

- Fixed _nogil.__exit__ return type from None to bool
- Fixed array.__class_getitem__ to pass n instead of item to cls()

Co-authored-by: da-woods <10536947+da-woods@users.noreply.github.com>

Split out "ShadowWithStubs"

Essentially I've decided not to do the subset which differs
significantly right now.

Disambiguate decorator types

since this was in the original Shadow.py
